00:33:09,100 --> 00:33:10,300
Which club did you join?

885
00:33:10,340 --> 00:33:11,860
The student council's art department.

886
00:33:13,430 --> 00:33:14,260
The arts department?

887
00:33:14,580 --> 00:33:15,710
Nice choice.

888
00:33:15,780 --> 00:33:16,950
Don't even try to leave.

889
00:33:18,260 --> 00:33:19,340
Lu.

890
00:33:19,990 --> 00:33:21,540
I have a feeling

891
00:33:22,060 --> 00:33:23,230
that Tian Chi

892
00:33:23,870 --> 00:33:25,500
likes you.

893
00:33:26,390 --> 00:33:27,870
Tian Chi is the most handsome guy

894
00:33:28,190 --> 00:33:29,020
in our faculty.

895
00:33:29,540 --> 00:33:30,580
He's top three in his major

896
00:33:30,660 --> 00:33:32,020
and has published in a core journal

897
00:33:32,230 --> 00:33:34,150
with his supervisor.

898
00:33:34,430 --> 00:33:35,260
He's even recommended

899
00:33:35,390 --> 00:33:36,950
by a professor for a postgraduate spot.

900
00:33:37,430 --> 00:33:39,780
He's such a perfect guy.

901
00:33:39,990 --> 00:33:41,020
What a catch!

902
00:33:42,670 --> 00:33:43,780
Stop talking nonsense.

903
00:33:44,020 --> 00:33:45,580
Who's talking nonsense?

904
00:33:45,680 --> 00:33:47,020
At the start of the semester,

905
00:33:47,190 --> 00:33:48,740
didn't he help you carry your luggage

906
00:33:48,820 --> 00:33:50,150
and give you his contact?

907
00:33:50,280 --> 00:33:52,560
That's just because we went
to the same high school.

908
00:33:52,640 --> 00:33:53,440
We're alumni.

909
00:33:53,480 --> 00:33:54,670
Then why did he

910
00:33:54,820 --> 00:33:57,430
accompany you
to the club recruitment today?

911
00:33:58,340 --> 00:33:59,910
He didn't accompany me.

912
00:33:59,950 --> 00:34:01,300
We just ran into each other.

913
00:34:01,390 --> 00:34:02,630
He ran into so many people,

914
00:34:02,630 --> 00:34:03,580
but why did he only

915
00:34:03,630 --> 00:34:04,430
accompany you?

916
00:34:04,910 --> 00:34:05,340
Li.

917
00:34:05,430 --> 00:34:06,230
Am I right?

918
00:34:06,340 --> 00:34:06,990
Yes.

919
00:34:07,190 --> 00:34:08,310
Look.

920
00:34:08,750 --> 00:34:10,270
People pursuing Qiu Li

921
00:34:10,270 --> 00:34:12,350
are lining up
from the West Campus to the East Campus.

922
00:34:12,350 --> 00:34:13,620
Even she thinks I have a point.

923
00:34:13,790 --> 00:34:15,100
What do you have to say now?

924
00:34:15,910 --> 00:34:16,540
According to

925
00:34:16,540 --> 00:34:17,390
your logic,

926
00:34:17,580 --> 00:34:18,270
shouldn't he

927
00:34:18,310 --> 00:34:19,350
like Qiu Li instead?

928
00:34:20,390 --> 00:34:21,180
Stop right there!

929
00:34:21,310 --> 00:34:22,660
He's not my type.

930
00:34:33,910 --> 00:34:35,270
Why are you turning off the aircon?

931
00:34:35,500 --> 00:34:36,830
It's not that hot.

932
00:34:37,000 --> 00:34:38,680
I think we should just turn on the fan.

933
00:34:38,990 --> 00:34:39,660
Why use a fan

934
00:34:39,660 --> 00:34:40,830
when we have an aircon?

935
00:34:41,100 --> 00:34:42,140
With the aircon on,

936
00:34:42,160 --> 00:34:43,580
the temperature inside gets too low,

937
00:34:43,580 --> 00:34:44,400
but outside it's hot.

938
00:34:44,440 --> 00:34:45,740
If we keep going in and out,

939
00:34:45,780 --> 00:34:46,760
we'll catch a cold.

940
00:34:46,780 --> 00:34:47,920
Plus, it wastes electricity.

941
00:34:48,830 --> 00:34:49,430
Well.

942
00:34:49,990 --> 00:34:52,350
If you don't want
to split the aircon bill

943
00:34:52,500 --> 00:34:53,950
because you're not here often,

944
00:34:54,220 --> 00:34:55,750
I'll pay for it myself.

945
00:34:56,100 --> 00:34:57,350
However, I get to decide

946
00:34:57,620 --> 00:34:58,660
when it's on.

947
00:35:02,660 --> 00:35:03,270
Why do you

948
00:35:03,310 --> 00:35:04,830
always boss people around?

949
00:35:04,910 --> 00:35:06,140
Just because you have money?

950
00:35:07,830 --> 00:35:08,700
What does this

951
00:35:08,790 --> 00:35:09,750
have to do with money?

952
00:35:09,780 --> 00:35:11,280
Can you stop making all of us suffer

953
00:35:11,400 --> 00:35:12,700
just because of you?

954
00:35:13,100 --> 00:35:14,140
It's fine.

955
00:35:14,420 --> 00:35:15,220
It's not that hot.

956
00:35:15,240 --> 00:35:16,420
We don't have to turn it on.

957
00:35:16,430 --> 00:35:16,830
Yes.

958
00:35:17,060 --> 00:35:18,390
We can wait until it gets hotter.

959
00:35:18,620 --> 00:35:20,140
Here, eat something.

960
00:35:20,310 --> 00:35:20,950
Don't be angry.

961
00:35:21,750 --> 00:35:22,470
Go ahead

962
00:35:22,580 --> 00:35:23,540
and sweat if you like.

963
00:35:24,540 --> 00:35:25,270
Li.

964
00:35:25,270 --> 00:35:26,000
You...

965
00:35:32,750 --> 00:35:33,470
Your phone.

966
00:35:35,700 --> 00:35:36,620
Let me take this call.

967
00:35:43,140 --> 00:35:44,270
Hello? Qi Qi.

968
00:35:45,500 --> 00:35:46,830
You finally remembered me.

969
00:35:47,790 --> 00:35:49,060
How's your new life?

970
00:35:51,580 --> 00:35:52,390
It's hard to explain.

971
00:35:53,060 --> 00:35:53,910
I thought university

972
00:35:53,950 --> 00:35:55,350
would be pretty chill,

973
00:35:56,140 --> 00:35:57,350
but I didn't expect

974
00:35:57,430 --> 00:35:58,620
so many frustrating things.

975
00:35:59,580 --> 00:36:00,500
What about Jing Xichi?

976
00:36:01,220 --> 00:36:02,220
He's something else.

977
00:36:02,350 --> 00:36:03,720
He actually tricked us for so long.

978
00:36:04,060 --> 00:36:04,750
Exactly.

979
00:36:05,100 --> 00:36:06,100
Even Song...

980
00:36:09,200 --> 00:36:10,840
Let's not talk about him anymore.

981
00:36:10,860 --> 00:36:11,350
Let's stop.

982
00:36:13,700 --> 00:36:14,310
It's okay.

983
00:36:15,750 --> 00:36:16,390
I've let it go.

984
00:36:19,270 --> 00:36:19,830
By the way,

985
00:36:20,620 --> 00:36:21,620
what are you doing?

986
00:36:22,350 --> 00:36:22,910
I...

987
00:36:23,860 --> 00:36:25,430
I'm waiting for a classmate to eat.

988
00:36:28,350 --> 00:36:28,990
I need to stop.

989
00:36:29,140 --> 00:36:30,260
He just finished class.

990
00:36:35,060 --> 00:36:35,660
He?

991
00:36:37,060 --> 00:36:37,750
Who is he?

992
00:37:42,870 --> 00:37:43,790
Why are you here?

993
00:37:44,660 --> 00:37:46,220
You've been in Jing City for so long

994
00:37:46,310 --> 00:37:47,270
and never contacted me.

995
00:37:50,830 --> 00:37:51,700
I'm just joking.

996
00:37:52,310 --> 00:37:53,270
I'm over

997
00:37:53,350 --> 00:37:54,180
all that.

998
00:37:55,310 --> 00:37:56,790
Since it's just the two of us

999
00:37:56,910 --> 00:37:57,990
studying in Jing City,

1000
00:37:58,350 --> 00:37:59,500
shouldn't we look out

1001
00:37:59,830 --> 00:38:00,390
for each other

1002
00:38:00,540 --> 00:38:01,430
as old classmates?

1003
00:38:04,580 --> 00:38:05,660
Are you free later?

1004
00:38:06,910 --> 00:38:08,830
I'm free.

1005
00:38:09,580 --> 00:38:10,350
Then come with me

1006
00:38:10,350 --> 00:38:12,340
to your university's
screening hall for a movie.

1007
00:38:13,310 --> 00:38:13,990
A movie?

1008
00:38:15,180 --> 00:38:15,910
Why not?

1009
00:38:16,500 --> 00:38:18,100
I rarely visit your campus.

1010
00:38:18,100 --> 00:38:19,470
Won't you even show me around?

1011
00:38:21,750 --> 00:38:22,310
Okay.

1012
00:38:23,020 --> 00:38:23,540
Let's go.

1013
00:38:45,270 --> 00:38:45,700
Who's that?

1014
00:38:45,910 --> 00:38:46,900
Why didn't you reply?

1015
00:38:47,580 --> 00:38:48,140
It's Du Wei.

1016
00:38:48,660 --> 00:38:50,790
She asked if I filled
out that application form.

1017
00:38:51,870 --> 00:38:53,140
Speaking of this, I'm curious.

1018
00:38:53,400 --> 00:38:55,140
Isn't that competition team pretty good?

1019
00:38:55,200 --> 00:38:56,540
Why are you so against joining?

1020
00:38:56,620 --> 00:38:57,760
It's too much hassle.

1021
00:38:58,040 --> 00:38:59,910
Not joining is more hassle, okay?

1022
00:39:00,390 --> 00:39:01,020
Du Wei

1023
00:39:01,020 --> 00:39:03,440
is famous for never giving up
until she gets what she wants.

1024
00:39:05,480 --> 00:39:07,060
What's that got to do with me?

1025
00:39:07,080 --> 00:39:08,900
Haven't you noticed
she's got her eye on you?

1026
00:39:12,620 --> 00:39:13,350
Keep going.

1027
00:39:14,320 --> 00:39:15,990
What exactly has she set her sights on?

1028
00:39:16,500 --> 00:39:17,910
Even if I'm the top student,

1029
00:39:18,100 --> 00:39:19,220
that's only among freshmen.

1030
00:39:19,560 --> 00:39:20,430
Even if we actually

1031
00:39:20,470 --> 00:39:21,830
join that competition,

1032
00:39:22,350 --> 00:39:23,220
we'll just end up

1033
00:39:23,270 --> 00:39:24,390
doing the hardest work.

1034
00:39:26,830 --> 00:39:27,270
That's it?

1035
00:39:27,990 --> 00:39:28,430
That's it.

1036
00:39:30,990 --> 00:39:31,580
Well.

1037
00:39:32,020 --> 00:39:33,500
Should I call you naive

1038
00:39:33,660 --> 00:39:34,620
or just plain dumb?

1039
00:39:34,990 --> 00:39:36,870
Haven't you noticed
the way she looks at you?

1040
00:39:37,020 --> 00:39:38,960
It's like she's about to
see right through you!

1041
00:39:42,020 --> 00:39:43,220
So by your logic,

1042
00:39:43,560 --> 00:39:45,620
since you pay
so much attention to her,

1043
00:39:45,950 --> 00:39:46,990
do you like her?

1044
00:39:47,880 --> 00:39:49,180
Can you not say things like that?

1045
00:39:49,180 --> 00:39:50,020
It'll bring bad luck.

1046
00:39:55,800 --> 00:39:56,960
What are you doing?

1047
00:39:57,380 --> 00:39:58,500
I'm working out now.

1048
00:39:58,540 --> 00:39:59,620
I have to strictly control

1049
00:39:59,700 --> 00:40:00,620
my daily fat intake.

1050
00:40:00,680 --> 00:40:02,580
It can only be 30%
of my total daily calories.

1051
00:40:03,180 --> 00:40:03,500
Okay.

1052
00:40:03,940 --> 00:40:05,270
I'll have some more of this then.

1053
00:40:06,350 --> 00:40:07,950
What exactly are you trying to do?

1054
00:40:09,220 --> 00:40:10,310
Let me educate you.

1055
00:40:10,990 --> 00:40:12,060
Based on my fitness plan,

1056
00:40:12,400 --> 00:40:14,180
not only do I need
to control my fat intake,

1057
00:40:14,220 --> 00:40:15,540
but I also have to consume

1058
00:40:15,540 --> 00:40:17,700
exactly 120 grams of protein a day.

1059
00:40:18,100 --> 00:40:18,830
I've already had

1060
00:40:20,470 --> 00:40:21,220
quite a bit.

1061
00:40:21,320 --> 00:40:23,220
I think I'm still short
by 15 or 16 grams.

1062
00:40:23,660 --> 00:40:24,990
What "15 grams"?

1063
00:40:25,280 --> 00:40:26,270
I need protein too!

1064
00:40:26,310 --> 00:40:27,020
Do you think

1065
00:40:27,060 --> 00:40:28,180
only you need protein?

1066
00:40:29,350 --> 00:40:29,790
Don't I?

1067
00:40:29,830 --> 00:40:30,870
I put in so much effort...

1068
00:40:32,790 --> 00:40:34,270
If I don't gain muscle, it's on you.

1069
00:40:51,600 --> 00:40:56,770
♪Fallen leaves flutter past your gaze♪

1070
00:40:58,560 --> 00:41:03,640
♪I dream of worlds within your days♪

1071
00:41:05,410 --> 00:41:10,760
♪Countless times,
I write your name in my heart♪

1072
00:41:11,070 --> 00:41:16,560
♪Wishes whispered to the stars above♪

1073
00:41:19,150 --> 00:41:24,170
♪How many faces in the glass I see♪

1074
00:41:25,960 --> 00:41:31,200
♪Time's gentle hand
pulling me out of my cocoon♪

1075
00:41:32,800 --> 00:41:38,220
♪Under the sun,
a rainbow butterfly takes flight♪

1076
00:41:38,680 --> 00:41:44,180
♪To rest upon your left shoulder bright♪

1077
00:41:45,380 --> 00:41:49,340
♪I still hear your promise in my ears♪

1078
00:41:49,340 --> 00:41:54,330
♪Before we said goodbye,
your spirit free♪

1079
00:41:54,460 --> 00:41:57,890
♪And full of life♪

1080
00:41:59,180 --> 00:42:02,640
♪If summer could last a little longer♪

1081
00:42:02,640 --> 00:42:07,750
♪Would regrets rewrite
where we'd gone wrong?♪

1082
00:42:08,010 --> 00:42:12,400
♪And let me be there with you
at the end of the story♪

1083
00:42:12,900 --> 00:42:16,800
♪Watching your silhouette from behind♪

1084
00:42:16,800 --> 00:42:21,740
♪My footsteps slow, we were too young♪

1085
00:42:21,740 --> 00:42:24,530
♪To know right from wrong♪

1086
00:42:26,440 --> 00:42:29,970
♪Your sweat-kissed face
I hold in my memory♪

1087
00:42:29,970 --> 00:42:33,220
♪Glows as bright as ever♪

1088
00:42:33,380 --> 00:42:39,140
♪I hope one day we'll meet again♪

1089
00:42:39,560 --> 00:42:44,160
♪At just the right time♪
